nginxRewriteTips: The URL Rewrite of Nginx is set here. Apache should set it in the project file
httpServerTips: Click to upload files or drag to the blank space to upload files
fileInfoTips: Drag the file here, or click to select the file
customVersionDirTips: Customize the version path, it will automatically find the executable file in the bin&sbin directory of this path.
hostsSaveFailed: System Hosts file failed to save. Please check whether the file exists and whether the file permissions are correct
hostsReadFailed: Failed to read the file /private/etc/hosts. Please check whether the file exists and whether the file permissions are correct
configNotFound: No config file found, please reselect the version
logFileNotFound: The log file does not exist
name: Name
killProcessConfirm: Are you sure to end the selected process?
killAllProcessConfirm: Are you sure to end all processes?
portNotUse: This port is not in use
sslMakeAlert: The SSL self-signed certificate is generated successfully, please find Dev Root CA {caFileName} in the opened keychain, and modify it to "always trust" the certificate
versionErrorTips: The version has been installed, but there is an error that prevents it from running, this problem is basically due to missing software dependencies or incorrect dependency version, try to run the command "brew update && brew upgrade" to fix it
fileBigErr: The file is too large, please select the correct configuration file
hostParseErr: The site failed to load, the original site data has been backed up to host.back.json, please check and repair the file in the opened folder
parkTips: Resolves subdomains if subdomain name is matching a subfolder name (Example: {subfoldername}.mydomain.tld)
parkConfirm: This will make all subfolders accessible as subdomain sites, do you want to continue?
ftpDirNotExists: Folder doesn't exist, please try again
staticDelAlert: In order to ensure the safe of user data, No longer provides the function of automatically deleting installed software. If you are sure you want to delete it, click OK. Manually delete the software in the open folder.
